cs.GT, cs.SI, cs.CY, cs.SOC, cs.LG

Reasoning: 
1. cs.GT (Computer Science and Game Theory) - The paper uses an evolutionary game-theoretic model to investigate the role of incentives in maintaining diversity in collective prediction. 
2. cs.SI (Social and Information Networks) - The paper discusses the challenges of maintaining diversity in the face of social pressure to imitate peers and proposes an incentive scheme to reward accurate minority predictions. 
3. cs.CY (Computers and Society) - The paper discusses the impact of incentives on collective intelligence and proposes a socially beneficial incentive scheme. 
4. cs.SOC (Social and Behavioral Sciences) - The paper investigates the role of incentives in maintaining diversity in collective prediction and discusses the social pressure to imitate peers. 
5. cs.LG (Machine Learning) - The paper discusses the use of collective intelligence for prediction and proposes an incentive scheme to optimize predictive accuracy.
